There was pomp and colour at the Madoka half Marathon this Saturday as hundreds turned out for the annual event.There was more fun as the athletics enthusiasts cheered British Deputy High Commissioner to Kenya, Andrew Bowels as he crossed the finish line in the half marathon race.The event is the brainchild of former Mwatate MP and Maj (Rtd) Marseden Madoka who is currently the chairman Kenya Ports Authority.Taita Taveta governor John Mruttu, Mwatate MP Andrew Mwadime, Taita Taveta women rep Joyce Lay and husband Bill Lay, Brookside Dairy regional manager Davies Mwangoma, athletics Kenya President Jackson Tuwei were among those present.